Film4.uk.title: Glass
Film4.uk.description: (2019) M. Night Shyamalan directs an all-star cast in this genre-bending superhero sequel. Three superhumans team up to escape a psychiatric ward. With Bruce Willis in a cagoule.

Film4.uk.title: Terminator Genisys
Film4.uk.description: (2015) Sci-fi thriller with Arnold Schwarzenegger and Emilia Clarke. Part five of the franchise follows Sarah Connor in an alternate timeline to the previous movies, as she takes on Skynet.

Film4.uk.title: The Black Arrow
Film4.uk.description: (1948) Historical adventure. A man (Louis Hayward) returns from the Wars of the Roses to learn from his uncle that a family friend has killed his father. But is everything as it seems?

Film4.uk.title: The Desert Fox
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Drama. James Mason stars in Henry Hathaway's sympathetic portrait of Field Marshal Erwin Rommel in the final years of his life during the Second World War. With Jessica Tandy.

Film4.uk.title: River of No Return
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Western with Robert Mitchum and Marilyn Monroe. An ex-con and a saloon singer steer a raft through hostile territory to face a showdown with her crooked fiancé. With Rory Calhoun.

Film4.uk.title: Dad's Army
Film4.uk.description: (1971) Film version of the popular comedy series set in 1940. The Walmington-on-Sea Home Guard, led by Arthur Lowe's Captain Mainwaring, bumble through a series of misadventures.

Film4.uk.title: Le Mans '66
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Oscar-winning sports drama starring Matt Damon and Christian Bale. In the 60s, Ford set out to build a car that can defeat Ferrari at the 24 Hours of Le Mans race.

Film4.uk.title: Daredevil
Film4.uk.description: (2003) Superhero fantasy. Ben Affleck is a blind lawyer who turns vigilante by night. Jennifer Garner plays his lover and Colin Farrell the villain who endangers them both. Strong violence.

Film4.uk.title: The Last Duel
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Historical drama from director Ridley Scott. Trial by combat is the only option to save a noblewoman's honour. With Jodie Comer, Matt Damon, Adam Driver and Ben Affleck.

Film4.uk.title: Wildfire
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Tense drama set near Northern Ireland's border. When two sisters are reunited after one had disappeared, their lives become increasingly complicated as old wounds start to open.

Film4.uk.title: Ten Tall Men
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Comedy adventure. Burt Lancaster stars as a Foreign Legion sergeant leading nine men on a dangerous mission to prevent a Berber attack on a North African desert fort.

Film4.uk.title: To Hell and Back
Film4.uk.description: (1955) Fact-based wartime drama. Audie Murphy, America's most decorated soldier in WWII, plays himself in this dramatic recreation of the valiant heroics that earned him the honours.

Film4.uk.title: Bohemian Rhapsody Interview...
Film4.uk.description: ...Special: Oscar-winning actor Rami Malek discusses playing Freddie Mercury in the rock biopic about the rise of the band Queen.

Film4.uk.title: Santa Fe
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Western starring Randolph Scott. Four brothers leave the defeated South to seek jobs as the US recovers from the Civil War. As one becomes a railwayman, the others turn to crime.

Film4.uk.title: Siege of the Saxons
Film4.uk.description: (1963) Dark ages adventure. King Arthur is murdered and usurped by his champion knight (Ronald Howard), so an outlaw (Ronald Lewis) seeks the mystic Merlin (John Laurie) to right the wrong.

Film4.uk.title: Steel Magnolias
